    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d683721b_0a5b3063",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/ext-location.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 126,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-11-09T18:23:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, from the end user point of view it is just strange to see blinking buttons (disabled/enabled) and a slight delay for nothing. Even more, for the user it\u0027s not clear why is the whole tab is enabled if there\u0027s no device :)\nI\u0027m ok with any way of doing it, but I would prefer if we (1) disabled the controls if there\u0027s no GPS device and (2) didn\u0027t do any work that we don\u0027t need",
      "parentUuid": "365a0ede_c8408f3c",
      "revId": "0d522cb9f60ee98bd9c364f72e25ae311da3064f",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
